I've just observed likely the same bug on relatively fresh -CURRENT after rebuilding misc/mc port in ncurses mode: END key no longer works when mc(1) run under screen(1).  This affects all ncurses programs which expect it be be KEY_END = 360.  This happens with GNU Screen versions 4.6.2 and 4.8.  On GNU/Linux, this bug does not occur (also tested against different versions).

The following small program can show if you keycode is wrong:

> #include <stdio.h>
> #include <ncurses.h>
> 
> void init(void)
> {
>     initscr();
>     raw();
>     keypad(stdscr, true);
>     noecho();
> }
> 
> int main()
> {
>     int c;
> 
>     init();
>     printw("press END key: ");
>     c = getch();
>     printf("%d (expected %d)\r\n", c, KEY_END);
>     endwin();
> }
press END key: 347 (expected 360)

CC'ing our sysutils/screen port maintainer as he might be interested as well.
